<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8156> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8156" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 184. In MRR 2.374, refer also to Liv. 39.33.1, and 52.4-5.\n" ;
	dprr:hasID 8156 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2434> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2434" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Colonized Graviscae (Liv. 40.29.2; cf. on Claudius, Elogium, CIL 1\n     .1, p. 200- Inscr. Ital. 13.3.70a)." ;
	dprr:hasID 2434 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2336> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2336" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Brut. 60; Liv. 39.32.5-13, and 44.11; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 48f., 122, 456f.; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod. The province for both was Liguria (Liv. 39.38.1 and 7). On Porcius, see D.- G. 5.98, no. 3." ;
	dprr:hasID 2336 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2335> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2335" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Added colonists to Cales (CIL 1\n     .1, p. 200- Inscr. Ital. 13.2.70a)." ;
	dprr:hasID 2335 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2290> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2290" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Election Liv. 38.42.3 Provinces and armies Liv. 38.42.6." ;
	dprr:hasID 2290 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2275> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2275" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "If Livy's text at 38.35.2 (P. Claudius) is correct, the career of P. Claudius affords the only example in this period of the continuation of curule offices (see 184 on Q. Fulvius Flaccus), since he is listed as Curule Aedile in 189. Mommsen (Str. 1.525, note 1), followed by Stella Maranca (306) and Maxis (42f.), suggests that Livy has interchanged his praetorship with that of his brother Ap. Claudius Pulcher, Cos. 185, who is listed as Praetor in 187. The order of their consulships supports Mommsen's view. Accordingly I list Ap. Claudius as Praetor in 188 and P. Claudius as Praetor in 187." ;
	dprr:hasID 2275 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2245> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2245" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 38.35.5." ;
	dprr:hasID 2245 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2244> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2244" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Münzer (RE no. 302) believes that P. Claudius Pulcher in Plin. NH 21.6 is a mistaken reference to a later C. Claudius Pulcher." ;
	dprr:hasID 2244 .
